   EVOLUTION _ On Wednesday, the Kansas Board of Education will
begin discussing proposed new science standards for public school
education and testing that call evolution a benchmark of science.
An alternate proposal, by a state board member, would change the
definition of science and list evolution as well as creationism as
theories. The alternate proposal was written mostly by people from
the Creation Science Association for Mid-America, who asked the
board member to propose it. By Kate Beem. Story will move in the
``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-ADOPT _ A couple from Kansas City is in China _ site of
anti-American and anti-NATO demonstrations _ trying to adopt a baby
and is staying not far from the American consulate. By Bill Graham.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
