732-390-4480, or fax her at 732-390-4697. If unable to reach Ms.
Weydert, please call 800-444-0267, or fax us at 816-822-1444.)  
  
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted twice _ into the
``a'' domestic/general news and ``k'' commentary news files.)  
  
 By MARCUS TANNER  
 c.1999 The Independent, London  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Q: WHY HAVE THE CHINESE TURNED AGAINST THEIR FORMER ALBANIAN
COMRADES? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A: The stoning of the Albanian embassy in Beijing by Chinese
protesters would have astonished Albania's former leader, Enver
Hoxha. Furious with Nikita Khrushchev's liberalizing policies in
the Soviet Union, and with his attacks on Stalin, Albania's former
