<P>
   CANADIAN STUDENTS _ Colleges and universities in the United
States are getting fewer students from Canada, thanks to the
exchange rate on money.
</P>
<P>
   PARTY PROMOTION _ ``Everybody parties,'' said a member of one of
New York's most active event promotion teams. ``It's all about
making sure everybody is having a great time. It's not all fun and
games, trying to throw parties in New York, but somebody's got to
do it, right?'' Apparently, more and more young entrepreneurs think
so. Black Diamonds Entertainment and other events groups, like
ProLinks Incorporated, Net2 and Partners in Soul, hold parties
several nights throughout the week at New York clubs like NV, the
Metronome, Vivid, Cream and Nell's, to name a few.
</P>
<P>
   DOG FAME _ Think your pooch oughta be in pictures? Well it's not
as easy or lucrative as it looks.
</P>
<P>
   DANCE SKATE _ In Central Park, disparate groups come together
with two things in common _ wheels and dance music. Black and
white, gay and straight, roller bladers and roller skaters all find
common ground in skate dancing.
</P>
<P>
   FLOWER BUSINESS _ Competition from Korean delis is squeezing
flower wholesalers in the plant district of New York.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET MANNERS _ The proper way to use email is being
addressed by an icon of gracious living _ Emily Post.
</P>
<P>
   24-HOUR GYM _ In the city that never sleeps, the need to work
out can be met at 1 a.m., 2 a.m., 3 a.m. or 4 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   GAY JEWS _ For orthodox Jews who are gay, the difficulties of
coming out are especially daunting. But support groups are forming
for those who are staunchly religious and gay.
</P>
<P>
   HISTORIC PHOTOS _ The century as seen through the eyes of
government
</P>
<P>
   SCHVITZING _ Russian immigrants have brought with them the
tradition of communal bathing along with a few swats with a broom.
</P>
