Sen. Phil Gramm in 1996 _ when Gramm raised $8 million in the first
three months of 1995, setting a record that Gore has just beaten.
 &HT;    Gramm too was a powerful fund-raiser, and he didn't even make it
to the primaries. As Koops puts it: ``'We've got the money' isn't a
good campaign message.''
 &HT;     c.1999 Jill Abramson  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Jill Abramson is Washington editor of The New York Times.) &LR;
</P>
