enrollment increased in the second year.
 &HT;    At the University of Texas, it dropped only slightly after
Hopwood went into effect. ``I don't think we can conclude that it's
impossible for even the flagship schools to get the numbers where
they were before the use of preferences,'' Pell says. In fact, the
