   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-THUMB (Undated) _ It is the rare writer whose journal
becomes literature. ``Under the Devil's Thumb'' shows that David
Gessner may be one such writer. By Michael Prager.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRAVEL (t) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-CANADA (Undated) _ People travel for four main reasons _
new destinations, new experiences, foreign flavor, and good value.
Canada has it all. By Jerry Morris. 660 words.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COLUMN &UR;  &LR; (Undated) _ The International Jazz Festival of
Montreal celebrates its 20th anniversary July 1 through 11 with
some new features including the sounds and tastes of Louisiana. By
Jerry Morris.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-NOTES (Undated) _ When you look at Canadian Martin
Fontaine, with his short hair and youthful appearance, the last
person you might think of is Elvis Presley. By Richard Carpenter.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-COLLINS (Key Biscayne, Fla.) _ Tricky Dick and Bebe _ was
that a sitcom with the laugh on us? _ are gone. But that doesn't
mean the island has lost its appeal. By Bud Collins.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Amazon did it with books; Ebay did
it with auctions. Can furniture.com do it with furniture? By Steven
Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ The convergence of telephone,
television, computer hardware, software, entertainment and Internet
services is just beginning. And Amos Hostetter regains his seat at
the table. By David Warsh.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ROSENBLATT (Undated) _ Seven years as a prizefighter have
changed wispy dreams into harsh realities for Dana Rosenblatt.
Broken hands. Dehydration. Broken promises. It adds up. By Ron
Borges. 1600 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) _ Patriots vice president Andy
Wasynczuk says parts of recent signing bonuses given to Ted
Johnson, Willie McGinest, Bruce Armstrong, and Chris Slade came
directly out of owner Bob Kraft's pocket. By Nick Cafardo. 800
words.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-COLUMN (Undated) _ Silverbulletday, who has won 10 of 11
career starts, really smoked Monday. By Ron Indrisano.
</P>
