the most private of literary figures, are about to be auctioned by
Sotheby's in a move likely to raise anew vexing questions about the
private rights of public figures. The letters were written between
April 25, 1972, and August 17, 1973, to the writer Joyce Maynard,
with whom Salinger carried on a nine-month romance that began when
she was an 18-year-old Yale University freshman and he was a
celebrated 53-year old author. By Peter Applebome.
