<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BREAUX CRITICIZES FELLOW DEMOCRATS ON MEDICARE REFORM
 &HT;    Moving in (w) Washington and (a) general news categories
 &HT;    By LARRY LIPMAN
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _The chairman of the failed Medicare reform
commission Tuesday lashed out at his fellow Democrats, charging
that many of them want a campaign issue more than real reform.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are clearly those who don't want to do anything on this,
and use this as a political issue,'' said Sen. John Breaux, D-La.,
