   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ROCKETS (Los Angeles) _ The Houston Rockets try to even
their first-round NBA playoff series in Game 2 against the Los
Angeles Lakers. By JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
<P>
   With: BKN-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BKN-FORUM (Los Angeles) _ Tuesday night's game could be the last
time the Houston Rockets ever play in the ``Fabulous'' Forum, the
site of so many memorable Rockets-Lakers confrontations over the
years. From Ralph Sampson's buzzer-beater in the Western Conference
finals in 1986 to the Rockets' infamous upset in 1981, the Forum
has witnessed some great moments in this rivalry. By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   With: BKN-LOPEZ-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ Sean Bergman makes his first home start
in more than a month as the Houston Astros play the Pittsburgh
Pirates at the Astrodome. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
