<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ It seems that a teen-ager's life is one big
government-created paradox. A 15-year-old is old enough to get a
job, yet too young to vote for the people who set the minimum wage.
Old enough to drive a vehicle, but too young to be out alone at
