   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., May 14) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE WILL INCLUDE MAP ILLUSTRATION
</P>
<P>
   UNEXPLORED LANDS: It's true that explorers have reached the
world's highest mountain (Everest, 29,029 feet) and the deepest
ocean (Mariana Trench, in the Pacific, 35,797 feet). And this might
suggest that the Earth is all explored. But at the dawn of a new
millennium, it's amazing to learn that some parts of the world
still haven't been charted. In fact, there's plenty of exploring
yet to be done _ parts of Antarctica, Canada's Northwest
Territories, the Himalayas and beyond. We interview folks at
National Geographic to learn where no human has gone before.
(Includes map of unexplored places.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (Available by 2 p.m., Thu., May 13) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE WILL INCLUDE SEVERAL COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE COLOR
ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   THE MAN BEHIND ``STAR WARS'': Filmmaker George Lucas talks about
the hype and the reality behind the biggest movie phenomenon of the
year, ``Episode I _ The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: PHANTOM MENACE COUNTDOWN: A 2-column color graphic
