   WITH: WINSTON CUP STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   WITH: BUSCH GRAND NATIONAL STANDINGS
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FOOD &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES NINE COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   CHEESES OF MEXICO: Cheeses are so integral to Mexican cooking
that it's hard to believe they're not native to the New World. Now
more North Americans are discovering these unique ``quesos.'' As
the Hispanic population has moved northward, and Mexican cuisine
gains in popularity nationwide, so has the interest in the
``quesos'' of Mexico. (Includes one 3-column color photo of a
Mexican cheese dish and six 1-column color photos of various kinds
of cheeses. Also, one color map of Mexico.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: RECIPES: Queso Derretido and Elote con Crema.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SKUBE ON BEER: The beers of Mexico are as familiar on this
side of the border as tacos and margaritas, from the amber,
toffee-ish Dos Equis to the thin and watery Corona. Less well-known
are the beers from elsewhere in Latin America. (Includes 1-column
color photo of three bottles of Latin American beers and 1-column
color photo of columnist.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHEELS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES TWO COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   PRERUNNER: Toyota is hardly a leader when it comes to building
and selling compact pickups, but the Tacoma PreRunner is proof that
the company is learning to play follow-the-leaders. (Includes
3-column color photo of the 1999 Toyota PreRunner.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE: Fact box previewing the 1999 Toyota PreRunner
compact rear-drive pickup.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: THE MECHANIC: Mild temperatures provide the perfect
opportunity to indulge in one of those traditional rites of spring
_ cleaning your car. (Includes 1-column color mug shot of
columnist.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PERSONAL TECHNOLOGY &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES THREE COLOR PHOTOS AND ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION
</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL CAMCORDERS: Just when you thought it was safe to
navigate the rough seas of which video camcorder to purchase, along
come digital video cameras. Well, why not? Everything else is
digital. (Includes one 3-column color illustration of a camcorder
riding a wave and a 2-column photo of the toolbox from Adobe's
video editing software.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECH BRIEFS: Even those folks who don't use Macs are
falling in love with Apple Computer. (Includes one 1-column color
photo of the Apple logo on an iMac computer.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY: If there were awards for worrying, you'd see
my picture on the cover of Time magazine accepting the trophy for
being the world champion. Today I worry you are worried about the
wrong things when it comes to the Year 2000 computer problem.
(Includes 1 column color sig of columnist.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: COMMENTARY: People are wondering how the tragedy at
Columbine High School could happen. I would suggest that we need to
pay close attention to our children's computer entertainment. I
think it's part of the problem. (Includes 2-column color photo of
woman mourning at a shrine set up near the site of the Colorado
school shooting.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRAVEL &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES FOUR COLOR PHOTOS, ONE COLOR MAP
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN: Travel books don't give much ink to this triumvirate of
beauty, known in the Japanese language as the ``Nihon Sankei.'' The
three natural sites are not the familiar cultural icons the world
associates with Japan. Yet, Japan's list is perfectly Japanese: It
embraces the inconspicuous and captures a subtle beauty. (Includes
3-column color photo of the red shrine at Miyajima, 3-column color
photo of the Bridge to Heaven, 18-pica color photo of the red
bridge at Matsushima, 18-pica color map illustration, 1-column
color photo of children cleaning their hands before entering a holy
shrine.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TRAVEL BRIEFS: Two former Yorkshire coal mines are the
unlikely site of a new British attraction that celebrates
environmental awareness.
