<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES 6 COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH TRAVEL: ``Dixie Before Disney: 100 Years of Roadside Fun''
is part history, part nostalgia trip. This oversize paperback
documents the era of tourism that faded when Walt Disney World
reared its mighty mouse ears in 1971.(Includes four color photos of
brochures and postcards from Southern tourist destinations such as
Stuckey's, Lookout Mountain, Frontier Land and Silver Springs.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW ``BELLA TUSCANY'' Frances Mayes' sequel to her
surprise best seller, ``Under the Tuscan Sun,'' wants to be a
travel book, a memoir, a cookbook and a set of interlacing essays
on living abroad and the Italian gift for happiness. This edition
of her quiet adventures does not integrate these goals as
successfully as her earlier book. (Includes 6-pica color photo of
book jacket.)
</P>
