<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990511.0287 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-11 19:21 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3003 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUSINESS &LR;      05-11 0304
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of May 12 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LITTON-AVONDALE (Los Angeles) _ The board of directors of
Avondale Industries agreed Tuesday to begin discussions with Litton
Industries over the Los Angeles-based company's $38-per-share offer
for Avondale. The board acknowledged that Litton's offer is sweeter
than a previous offer from Newport News and worth pursuing. Last
week, Litton made separate, unexpected bids for Avondale and
Newport News that, if successful, would make Litton the preeminent
military ship contractor in the U.S. By Greg Wilcox. (Will move in
the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-ENTREPRENEUR (Los Angeles) _ To Tom O'Malia, successful
entrepreneurship is all about recognizing and seizing the right
opportunity to launch a new venture. So it is with teaching, says
O'Malia, director of the Lloyd Greif Center for Entrepreneurial
Studies at the University of Southern California's Marshall School
of Business. By Enrique Rivero.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-JUDGMENT (Los Angeles) _ Warner Bros. received a $3.6
million judgment against Los Angeles-based company that was
counterfeiting the Burbank-based company's Looney Tunes and DC
Comics merchandise. The principals of the company were also found
by a U.S. Federal District Judge to have violated two previous
orders prohibiting them from engaging in the sale of counterfeit
products. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news
file.)
</P>
