competitive satellite launching industry. In the last nine months,
there have been six significant failures of U.S. rockets trying to
put civilian and military payloads into orbit, resulting in losses
totaling $3.5 billion. Engineers studying the problem say they
cannot tell if the recent difficulties are just bad luck or signs
of systemic problems in the launching business. By Warren E. Leary.
(Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.) 2,000
words.
