it produced by Vietcong photographers who lived for years in
jungles not far from Saigon. And now, for the first time, the films
are going on the market. In an unusual post-Cold War deal, the
Vietnamese government has teamed with a German company to market
broadcasting and movie rights to foreign companies. By Edmund L.
Andrews. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
