<P>
   AMAZON-PRIVACY (Seattle) _ Amazon.com has leapt into many happy
investors' portfolios by selling more books online than anyone
else. The world's largest Internet retailer may now be poised to
start trading in a more controversial item: Personal information on
its customers.
</P>
