<P>
   RIDING-DISABLED (Seattle) _ Margo O'Callaghan of Seattle is one
of five disabled riders selected to participate in this year's
Bradshaw Challenge at the U.S. Equestrian Team's Gladstone Festival
of Champions next month. The pretigious event showcases some of the
country's top able-bodied and disabled riders in seven equestrian
disciplines; it's also a qualifier for national and world
championships.
</P>
<P>
   By Judi Hunt. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   RAMSEY-COLUMN (Seattle) _ Do you have freedom of speech if
you're talking to a machine? Last week the Ninth Circuit Court of
Appeals ruled in Bernstein v. Dept. of Justice case that you do.
The ruling was a milestone in the commercial use of encryption.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-TRIPPIN' (Seattle) _ ``Trippin''' is another in a line of
recent movies that are dull variations on the theme of high school
boy/girl wants girl/boy, gets boy/girl through subversive method,
then loses girl/boy and ends up making up with boy/girl at the
senior prom. They're an insult to everyone.
