<HEADLINE>
U S WEST NAMES CEO SOLOMON TRUJILLO AS CHAIRMAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   U S West Inc. said Tuesday that Solomon Trujillo, the local
phone carrier's chief executive, had been elected chairman.
</P>
<P>
   While U S West is the smallest of the Baby Bell local phone
giants, Trujillo's elevation may make it the biggest company in the
nation with a Hispanic chairman.
</P>
<P>
   Trujillo, 47, took over the job from Richard McCormick, 58, who
stepped down and was elected chairman emeritus.
</P>
<P>
   Trujillo takes over U S West at a moment when most of the
nation's other big phone companies are busy consolidating. Of the
seven original Baby Bells, only five remain, and U S West and
BellSouth Corp. are the only two that have not participated in
multibillion-dollar mergers.
</P>
<P>
   With its largely rural service region, which includes the Rocky
Mountain states and the Dakotas, U S West has long failed to match
the financial performance of the other Bells. But it has been the
leader among them in deploying high-speed Internet service using an
advanced phone technology called digital subscriber line. And the
logistical problems in serving many of its customers may help
protect it from competition from new local phone companies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
