<SLUG> BC-SPRINGER-ARREST-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TV DRAGNET NABS FUGITIVE DRAG QUEEN ON `JERRY SPRINGER SHOW' 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By LISA TEACHEY 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ A recent guest on the ``Jerry Springer Show'' may be
watching future episodes of the slugfest talk program from behind
bars.
</P>
<P>
   Willie Johnson, 22, was arrested Monday in Louisiana as he and
family members gathered at a relative's house to watch the national
broadcast of an episode about drag queens, featuring Johnson and
his sister Veronica.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson, who uses the aliases Alicia, Poppy, Christina and John,
is charged in Harris County, Texas, with aggravated assault with a
deadly weapon. He is accused of stabbing Reginald Hickman in the
neck last month in southeast Houston.
</P>
<P>
   The show featuring Johnson, wearing a skimpy green dress, was
taped earlier and aired Monday _ at the same time Houston homicide
detectives John Burmester and Brian Harris were on the phone with
authorities in Louisiana trying to track him down.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just happened to call on the day all of this was
happening,'' Harris said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   His partner was on the phone with police in Lecompte, La.,
Harris said, while he was talking to authorities in Cheneyville,
La.
</P>
<P>
   ``My partner gave the officer a description of Johnson and the
officer laughed and said, `I think he's on TV right now,'`` Harris
said.
</P>
<P>
   The dispatcher in Cheneyville also was watching the show. ``She
said, `They're (Johnson and his sister) on TV right now
fighting,''' Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just looked at each other and said `This is
unbelievable.'''
</P>
<P>
   Apparently most people in both of the small towns between
Alexandria and Lafayette in south-central Louisiana knew Johnson
and were tuned in to catch his act on the show.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson was quickly arrested at his family's home in Rapides
Parish _ in front of the gathering of relatives.
</P>
<P>
   The detectives were still trying Monday to determine whether
Johnson taped the show before or after the stabbing. &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; Since Johnson was on parole for a felony forgery conviction, he
will be held without bail after his return to Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson allegedly stabbed Hickman with a paring knife April 11
during an argument between Hickman and Johnson's sister.
</P>
<P>
   The couple, who Harris said were common-law husband and wife,
were arguing and she called her brother, Johnson, to come pick her
up. When Johnson arrived, Hickman followed the woman to the car.
Johnson stabbed him as he was trying to prevent her from leaving,
police say.
</P>
<P>
   Hickman almost died from the wound in his neck and he may be
permanently paralyzed.
</P>
<P>
   Harris and Burmester had been looking for Johnson since April 16
and had talked to his mother in Houston. They even received a call
from Johnson, who said he was going to turn himself in.
</P>
<P>
   ``We gave him some time to see if he was a man of his word, but
he never showed up,'' Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   ``When they (the Louisiana officers) told us they were watching
him on TV we thought `You gotta be kidding,''' Harris said. ``This
definitely goes into our memorable file.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
