-- ``And You Will Do As You Are Told,'' reads a campaign billboard
for the Shas Party hanging over a major street in the southern
Israeli city. The poster reminds Shas supporters to follow
instructions on whom to vote for in upcoming elections issued by
party leaders, mostly rabbis. With less than a week to go before
the election, a trip through southern Israel finds voters more
interested in issues and less interested in personalities. (Rina
Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
