<SLUG> BC-KOSOVO-CHINA-EMAIL-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHINA PROTEST KNOCKS OUT WHITE HOUSE WEB SITE 
</HEADLINE>
  (rk) 
 By DAVID STOUT   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The White House site on the World Wide Web has been
overwhelmed _ quite literally _ with e-mail from China protesting
the accidental NATO bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
   The site was knocked out of commission late Monday afternoon
when the number of electronic messages was more than it could bear,
Mike Hammer, a spokesman for the National Security Council, said
Tuesday. It was still down Tuesday evening, said Hammer, who said
he could not predict when it would be in operation again.
</P>
<P>
   The problem was discovered when White House aides could not log
on to the Internet, and it was diagnosed by White House computer
experts, Hammer said. Since the White House site
(www.whitehouse.gov) runs on an independent system, no other White
House computer systems were affected.
</P>
<P>
   Hammer said the web site had been knocked out before for short
periods, but always because of technical problems, never by the
sheer volume of correspondence. He said there was no way to know
how many messages had been sent, but that the enormous volume was a
sign of hope, in a way.
</P>
<P>
   ``All those users can access and receive our information,'' he
said. ``It works both ways.''
</P>
<P>
   The population of Internet users is growing very rapidly in
China, as almost everywhere else. By some estimates, there are 2.1
million Internet accounts, many with multiple users, in the
country, and some computer authorities predict there will be 4
million accounts by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
   Chinese hackers invaded and defaced the web site for the U. S.
Embassy in Beijing, the official China Daily reported Tuesday. The
newspaper said the hackers inserted the phrase ``Down With the
Barbarians'' into the embassy's home page and replaced an image of
Ambassador James Sasser with the same phrase in Chinese characters.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
